---
import MainNav from '../../components/MainNav.astro';

const chamberPaths = [
  {
    title: "The Law of Return",
    href: "/labyrinth/law-of-return",
    label: "First Chamber",
    description:
      "The governing threshold: return before reaching, presence before interpretation, and depth without losing the center.",
  },
  {
    title: "Operating Systems",
    href: "/labyrinth/operating-systems",
    label: "Second Chamber",
    description:
      "How Ashvault thinks: routing, recursion, signal, state, and the difference between architecture and archive.",
  },
  {
    title: "Sealed Reliquary",
    href: "/labyrinth/sealed",
    label: "Deeper Descent",
    description:
      "Relics and chambers that require controlled approach. Not hidden from worthiness; protected from careless arrival.",
  },
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>The Labyrinth - Ashvault</title>    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --maze-black: #050505;
        --path-gray: #1a1a1a;
        --wall-dark: #0f0f0f;
        --thread-silver: #9a9aaa;
        --guide-gold: #c4a76f;
        --labyrinth-font: "Cinzel", serif;
      }

      :global(*) {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      :global(body) {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: var(--labyrinth-font);
        background: var(--maze-black);
        color: var(--thread-silver);
        min-height: 100vh;
        overflow-y: auto;
      }

      .maze-space {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem) clamp(1rem, 4vw, 2rem);
      }

      .corridor {
        position: relative;
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.2);
        border-radius: 12px;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(15, 15, 15, 0.9), rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.95));
        box-shadow: 0 0 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9), inset 0 0 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
        letter-spacing: 0.15rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        text-align: center;
      }

      .entrance-text {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--thread-silver);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
      }

      .passage {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-left: 2px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.3);
        background: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }

      .chamber-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin: 2.5rem 0;
      }

      .chamber-card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        min-height: 220px;
        padding: 1.35rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.22);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(17, 17, 20, 0.82), rgba(6, 6, 8, 0.9));
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: transform 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
      }

      .chamber-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
        border-color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.58);
        background: linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(28, 24, 17, 0.88), rgba(8, 8, 10, 0.94));
      }

      .chamber-label {
        color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.72);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.14rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .chamber-card h2 {
        margin: 0.85rem 0 0.8rem;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }

      .chamber-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.88);
        line-height: 1.65;
      }

      .passage h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.08rem;
      }

      .passage p {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.9);
      }

      .sealed-entry {
        margin: 1.5rem 0;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.15);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.6);
        text-align: center;
      }

      .sealed-entry h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.7);
        letter-spacing: 0.1rem;
      }

      .sealed-entry p {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.7);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-style: italic;
      }

      .lock-symbol {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        opacity: 0.6;
      }

      .thread-mark {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        opacity: 0.5;
        filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.2));
      }

      .vault-paths {
        margin: 3rem 0 2rem;
        padding: 2rem;
        background: rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.5);
        border: 1px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.2);
        border-radius: 12px;
      }

      .vault-paths h2 {
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.1rem;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .path-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .path-link {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1rem;
        padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
        background: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.6);
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.15);
        border-radius: 8px;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
      }

      .path-link:hover {
        background: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.1);
        border-color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.4);
        transform: translateX(6px);
      }

      .path-icon {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }

      .path-text {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.25rem;
      }

      .path-text strong {
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.05rem;
      }

      .path-text span {
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.8);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        .corridor {
          padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 2.5rem);
        }

        .entrance-text {
          font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .passage {
          padding: 1rem;
        }

        .passage h2 {
          font-size: 1.25rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="maze-space">
      <MainNav />
      <main class="corridor">
        <h1>The Labyrinth</h1>

        <p class="entrance-text">
          Into the depths of Calyxion. The Labyrinth is not the archive and not the
          public bridge. It is the threshold system: the place where depth is tested
          before the locked rooms answer.
        </p>

        <div class="passage">
          <h2>The Nature of the Maze</h2>
          <p>
            The Labyrinth is not confusion. It is controlled complexity. Each turn asks
            whether the seeker can hold return, signal, contradiction, and consequence
            without collapsing them into something easier.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is not a puzzle to be solved. It is a path of approach. The deeper you go,
            the more the rooms ask what kind of hand is reaching.
          </p>
        </div>

        <section class="chamber-grid" aria-label="Labyrinth chambers">
          {
            chamberPaths.map((chamber) => (
              <a class="chamber-card" href={chamber.href}>
                <span class="chamber-label">{chamber.label}</span>
                <h2>{chamber.title}</h2>
                <p>{chamber.description}</p>
              </a>
            ))
          }
        </section>

        <div class="passage">
          <h2>How the Path Works</h2>
          <p>
            The Labyrinth does not replace the Black Vault. It prepares the descent.
            Its chambers teach approach, return, and system behavior before the sealed
            rooms below are treated as doors instead of prizes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <nav class="vault-paths" aria-label="Black Vault pathways">
          <h2>Descend Deeper</h2>
          <div class="path-links">
            <a class="path-link" href="/black-vault-gate">
              <span class="path-icon">🪞</span>
              <span class="path-text">
                <strong>The Black Vault</strong>
                <span>All hidden chambers and sealed knowledge</span>
              </span>
            </a>
            <a class="path-link" href="/black-vault-gate/sealed-relics">
              <span class="path-icon">🔐</span>
              <span class="path-text">
                <strong>Sealed Relics</strong>
                <span>Artifacts awaiting the right invocation</span>
              </span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </nav>

        <div class="thread-mark" aria-hidden="true">∞ ⚝ ∞</div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
